sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client, DB: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Access (Authenticated)

    Client->>Router: HTTPS/443<br/>TLS (edge)
    Router->>KRBP: HTTPS/8443<br/>TLS (reencrypt)
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorization result
    KRBP->>REST: HTTP/8080<br/>plaintext (localhost)<br/>pre-authorized
    REST->>DB: 5432/3306 TCP<br/>Configurable TLS<br/>password auth
    DB-->>REST: Query results
    REST-->>KRBP: Response
    KRBP-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client, DB: Flow 2: Operator Reconcile Loop

    participant Operator as Operator Controller

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (ModelRegistry CR)<br/>HTTPS/TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: CRUD operations<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS<br/>ServiceAccount token
    Note right of Operator: Creates: Deployments, Services,<br/>Routes, NetworkPolicies,<br/>Roles, RoleBindings,<br/>ServiceAccounts, Groups

    Note over Client, DB: Flow 3: Model Catalog Data Population

    participant CatalogInit as Init Containers<br/>catalog-data-init<br/>benchmark-data-init
    participant Catalog as Catalog Container<br/>8080/TCP
    participant CatDB as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    CatalogInit->>CatalogInit: Write data to<br/>emptyDir volume
    Note right of CatalogInit: catalog-data-init &<br/>benchmark-data-init
    Catalog->>Catalog: Read ConfigMap volumes<br/>(catalog sources)
    Catalog->>CatDB: PostgreSQL/5432<br/>password auth
    CatDB-->>Catalog: Stored catalog data
